	  lame

2008-09-25 10:36  kelnos

	* settings/backdrop-list-manager.c,
	  settings/backdrop-list-manager.h:
	  ditch old backdrop list manager dialog files

2008-09-25 06:28  kelnos

	* NEWS, src/xfce-desktop.c, src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c:
	  implement rubber band selection for XfdesktopIconView (bug 3245)

2008-09-25 06:27  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c:
	  remove redundant function

2008-09-25 06:27  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c:
	  remove unneeded glib 2.10 check since we depend on 2.12 now

2008-09-25 06:27  kelnos

	* src/xfce-desktop.c:
	  double-buffer the desktop window again.
	  
	  i'm not entirely sure why we turned this off years and years
	  ago. it
	  doesn't really impact performance (well, except for positively)
	  or
	  memory usage, and fixes a bunch of flicker issues i never got
	  around to
	  fixing.

2008-09-25 06:27  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c:
	  remove custom desktop tooltip code. it was always slightly
	  buggy, and
	  working on the icon view code was made much more difficult
	  because of
	  it. gtk 2.12 is required for desktop icon tooltips.

2008-09-20 18:45  kelnos

	* configure.ac.in:
	  autoconf sucks. specifically, new versions that change behavior
	  suck.

2008-09-20 05:47  kelnos

	* NEWS:
	  update NEWS

2008-09-20 05:43  kelnos

	* modules/menu/desktop-menu.c:
	  various coding style fixes and little code cleanups

2008-09-20 05:43  kelnos

	* modules/menu/desktop-menu.c:
	  fix menu module crash on .desktop file change or icon theme
	  change (bug 3615)
	  
	  this also fixes the weird "double menu" problem (bug 4342). what
	  was
	  happening was that thunar-vfs was firing off a dir change
	  notification,
	  and then the menu would start to regenerate. then it would call
	  into
	  GtkIconTheme, which then noticed that the icon cache was stale
	  and
	  needed to be re-read. so then it would fire
	  GtkIconTheme::changed,
	  which causes a recursive menu regeneration. since the menu
	  generation
	  function isn't reentrant, now we use g_idle_add() to schedule a
	  menu
	  regen, and we don't schedule one if there's one already
	  scheduled or
	  in progress.

2008-09-16 05:07  kelnos

	* NEWS, src/xfce-desktop.c, src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c:
	  add XDG userdir support for desktop and templates folders
	  
	  patch somewhat from Andrea Santilli <yawara@quipo.it> (bug 4365)

